War
- 52 cards, divide amongst two cards
- each player flips a card
 - the player with the higher card takes both cards
 - if the cards match
  - each player seperates three cards (or as many as they have remaining if they have three or less)
  - the top card after those three is then drawn and the player with the higher card takes all of the cards
  - if there is a tie, the "war" process is repeated
- the game is won when one player has all of the cards

Objects Needed
- Card class
- Deck class
- Player class
- Game class


A game has players
A player has a Deck
A deck has cards
